ce:section.ce:para:
Under optimal conditions, the constructed Au-Arg-Thr-GQD sensor was used for the determination of different concentrations of IMI. Fig. 5
                         shows the DPV response curves of IMI at different concentrations. The peak current increased with the increase of IMI concentration, and showed a good linear relationship in the concentration range of 0.1–20 μM. The linear equation is Ip (μA) = −0.6925 CIMI-1.417, R2 = 0.9994, and the detection limit was 0.011 μM. Compared with the reported electrochemical analysis methods (Table 1
                        ), the constructed Au-Arg-Thr-GQD sensor showed high sensitivity to IMI. This is attributed to the introduction of Arg-Thr-GQD, which improves the electrocatalytic active site of Au nanoparticles, thus bringing high catalytic activity. Further, the interconnection between Arg-Thr-GQD and Au nanoparticles forms a three-dimensional conductive network, which increases the rate of electron conduction. In addition, the synergistic effect between Au nanoparticles and Arg-Thr-GQD further improves the catalytic activity.
